					<div id="venue-description">
						<p>
							Nestled in eastern Carlsbad, Leo Carrillo Ranch is a Historical &amp; National Park located approximately 40 miles north of San Diego.  Once a vacation ranch to actor Leo Carrillo, of mid 1950’s Hollywood fame, the park is meticulously landscaped and home to free roaming peacocks, and over 4 miles of walking trails.
						</p>
						<address>
							Leo Carrillo Ranch<br>
							6200 Flying Leo Carrillo Lane<br>
							Carlsbad, CA 92113<br>
							<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Leo+Carrillo+Ranch+Historic+Park/@33.1189606,-117.2371139,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x94f7d5714196d1a" target="_blank">View in Google Maps</a>
						</address>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p>
					Both the ceremony and the reception will be held outdoors, so we recommend wearing layers to be comfortable in the afternoon sun, and also once the sun goes down. The 27 acres of this historical park is made of irregular earthen and paved surfaces. It is recommended that you wear appropriate shoes for the uneven terrain. With the exception of immediate family members, we ask that no young children attend the ceremony or reception.
				</p>
				<p>
					The venue has a large parking lot, and there is ample space to park. It is a brief walk to the estate where the ceremony will be held, so please allow at least 5 minutes after parking to make your way to the ceremony. We encourage you to arrive early to explore the grounds and attempt to take a <a class="instagram-link" href="instagram://tag?name=peacockselfie" target="_blank"><span class="hashtag">#peacockselfie</span></a>.  There is no overnight parking allowed at the ranch, thus all cars must be moved by 11pm. Our reception will be over by 9pm. Look into taking <a href="#bus">provided transportation here</a>.
				</p>
			</div>
